# Task 11 – UI Policy Configuration

## Project

**Virtual Agent–Driven SLA Breach Awareness & Justification System**

---

## Objective

This task configures a UI Policy to dynamically display and enforce SLA-related fields when an Incident is marked as **SLA At Risk**.

---

## Navigation

**System UI → UI Policies**

---

## Condition

| Field | Value |
|------|------|
| SLA At Risk | True |

---

## UI Policy Actions

| Field | Visible | Mandatory |
|------|---------|-----------|
| SLA Breach Reason | Yes | Yes |
| SLA Breach Justification | Yes | Yes |
| SLA Acknowledgement | Yes | No |

---

## Deliverables

- UI Policy
- UI Policy Actions
- Incident Form Configuration
- Screenshots

---

## Expected Outcome

When **SLA At Risk** is set to **True**, the required SLA fields become visible and mandatory, ensuring complete SLA breach documentation before incident closure.

---

## Status

**Completed**

---

**Internship:** SmartBridge – ServiceNow Administration

**Task:** 11 – UI Policy Configuration
